message.content:
1. The Global Aesthetic Improvement Scale was used to measure improvement in subjects.
2. The proportion of subjects reporting improvement with CPM-26 was 97.7% at 3 months.
3. The proportion of subjects reporting improvement with VYC-20 was 88.6% at 3 months.
4. The proportion of subjects reporting improvement with CPM-26 was 73.8% at 12 months.
5. The proportion of subjects reporting improvement with VYC-20 was 71.1% at 12 months.
6. The proportion of subjects reporting improvement with CPM-26 was 61.0% at 18 months.
7. The proportion of subjects reporting improvement with VYC-20 was 56.7% at 18 months.
8. The measurements were taken at 3 months, 12 months, and 18 months.

messages.content:
Statement: The proportion of subjects reporting improvement on the Global Aesthetic Improvement Scale compared with baseline for CPM-26 and VYC-20 was 97.7% and 88.6%, respectively, at 3 months, 73.8% and 71.1% at 12 months, and 61.0% and 56.7% at 18 months.
